# Interpreter for _openvpn_dump0 - OpenVPN protocol database dump
#
# The openvpn dump function generates executable shell commands for recreating
# OpenVPN configs, categories, and links. It produces output for capture/piping.
#
# Type: Non-terminal function (produces data for consumption by other commands)
# Default: cat (output to stdout for capture/piping)
#
# Usage:
#   vpn-switch openvpn dump > openvpn-backup.sh  # Save OpenVPN-only dump
#   vpn-switch dump > full-backup.sh                 # Full dump (calls openvpn dump)
#
# Override examples:
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_openvpn_dump=tee /tmp/ovpn-dump.log  # Output and log
#   VPN_SWITCH_INTERPRETER_openvpn_dump=cat  # Default (explicit)
#
# Note: This is called by _dump0, which handles the prologue/epilogue.
# The openvpn dump focuses only on protocol-specific commands.
